          <title>Spurgeon breaks 33-game scoreless streak with two goals, Minnesota beats Chicago 3-2</title>
          <description><![CDATA[ST. PAUL, Minn. (AP) — Jared Spurgeon ended a 33-game scoring drought with two of Minnesota’s three second-period goals and the Wild beat the Chicago Blackhawks 3-2 on Friday. Marco Rossi also scored for Minnesota and Marc-Andre Fleury, who turned 40 on Thursday, made 20 saves to improve to 5-0-1.]]></description>
